    "ShiftFromTo": "Shift(From - To)",
    "CalculationWay": "Shift Type",
    "IsLimited": "Is Limited",
    "Action": "Action",
    "Notes": "<br><strong><i><u>Code : </u></i></strong>Enter the code required to be assigned to the attendance plan. <br><br><strong><i><u>Latin Name : </u></i></strong>Enter the description of the Shift in English <br><br><strong><i><u>Arabic Name : </u></i></strong>Enter the description of the Shift in Arabic <br><br><strong><i><u> Is Dayoff : </u></i></strong> Mark this check box in case the shift is in the weekend or day off.<br><br><strong><i><u> Is Default : </u></i></strong> Mark this check box in case the shift will be assigned to the employees when hired by default till it is being modified if required.<br><br><strong><i><u> static-variable ,free , calculated: </u></i></strong>to set the shift type which is linked to similar plan type     <br><br><strong><i><u> static-variable: </u></i></strong>Static fixed hours (e.g. from 8 am to 5 pm).  <br><br><strong><i><u> Is Calculated Shift : </u></i></strong>Mark this check box in case you will pay the employees assigned to the shift according to the actual working hours based on each employee’s hour rate.<br><br><strong><i><u> Is Free Shift : </u></i></strong>Mark this check box in case the shift depends on specific number of hours that the employees should spend at work without setting fixed times and the following field will be activated:<br><br><strong><i><u>• Shift Hours : </u></i></strong> Number of hours that the employees should spend at work.<br><br><strong><i><u>Allowance sign hours:</u></i></strong> The time allowed to register the out fingerprint since the beginning of the employee's entry<br><br><strong><i><u>Shift Type: </u></i></strong>Specify the type of the shift; whether a morning shift or a night shift or overnight by marking one of the attached radio buttons.<br><br><strong><i><u>Allowed Overtime Hours: </u></i></strong>Enter the number of hours of the overtime allowed for the employees in the shift after which the employee will not be paid for any extra hours <br><br><strong><i><u> From Time : </u></i></strong>Enter the time in which the employees should attend in the shift; either manually or by clicking on the clock shape located at the left side of the field and selecting from the list.  <br><br><strong><i><u>To Time: </u></i></strong>Enter the time in which the employees should leave in the shift; either manually or by clicking on the clock shape located at the left side of the field and selecting from the list <br><br><strong><i><u>Allowed Late Time (Minutes): <br></u></i></strong>Enter the time after which the late attendance of the employees in the shift will not be allowed (in minutes). <br><br><strong><i><u>Allowed Early Leave (Min.):<br></u></i></strong>Enter the time before which the early leave of the employees in the shift will not be allowed (in minutes). <br><br><strong><i><u>Finger Start From : </u></i></strong>Enter the time in which the employees will be allowed to register the attendance fingerprint in the shift. <br><br><strong><i><u> Finger End In:</u></i></strong>Enter the time after which the employees will not be allowed to register the attendance fingerprint in the shift.<br><br><strong><i><u>Break Start:<br></u></i></strong>Enter the time in which the employees break starts either manually or by clicking on the clock shape located at the left side of the field and selecting from the list<br><br><strong><i><u>Break End:<br></u></i></strong>Enter the time in which the employees break ends either manually or by clicking on the clock shape located at the left side of the field and selecting from the list<br><br><strong><i><u>Is Nursing:</u></i></strong><u><i>allowed shift to display in nursing module</i></u>",
    "ShiftNotes": "<br><strong><i><u>Code : </u></i></strong>Display the code required to be assigned to the attendance plan. <br><br><strong><i><u>Name : </u></i></strong>Display the description of the Shift <br><br><strong><i><u> Shift From : <br></u></i></strong>Display the time in which the employees should attend in the shift<br><br><strong><i><u> Shift To : <br></u></i></strong>Display the time in which the employees should leave in the shift<br><br><strong><i><u>Nature: </u></i></strong>Specify the type of the shift whether a morning shift or a night shift <br><br><strong><i><u>Condition: </u></i></strong>Shows wehther the shift is Vacation or Nursing or both <br><br><strong><i><u> Is Dayoff : </u></i></strong>  in case the shift is in the weekend or day off. <br><br><strong><i><u>Calculation Way: </u></i></strong>Display the method of calculating the working hours in the attendance plan whether is one of the following : <br><br><i><u>• Static: </u></i>The employees fixed hours (e.g. from 8 am to 5 pm). <br><br><i><u>• Variable: </u></i>The employees variable hours (e.g. from 8 am to 5 pm with the exception of coming late with the condition of substituting these hours during the week or the month according to the selection). <br><br><i><u>• Calculated: </u></i>Calculating the number of working hours for the employee and pay them according to each employee’s hour rate. <br><br><i><u>• Free: </u></i>Specify the number of hours that the employees should spend at work without setting fixed times. ",
    "Active": "Active",
    "applyMultiRanges": "Apply Multi Ranges",
    "DirectRange": "Direct Range"
  },
