    "HeaderNotes": "<br />\n <br />\n<strong>\n\n<i> <u> note:</u> \n</strong></i> <strong><i><u>Data displayed according to the user's authority with departments .<br><br><strong><i><u> Plan:</u></i></strong> Display the description of the attendance plan <br><br><strong><i><u>Plan Type: </u></i></strong>Select the method of calculating the working hours in the attendance plan by marking one of the attached radio buttons:<br><br><strong> <i><u>• Static Hours :</u></i></strong> The employees fixed hours (e.g. from 8 am to 5 pm). <br><br><strong><i><u>• Variable Hours </u></i></strong>The employees variable hours (e.g. from 8 am to 5 pm with the exception of coming late with the condition of substituting these hours during the week or the month according to the selection <br><br><strong><i><u>• Calculated Hours : </u></i></strong>Calculating the number of working hours for the employee and pay them according to each employee’s hour rate. <br><br><strong><i><u>• Free Hours : </u></i></strong>Specify the number of hours that the employees should spend at work without setting fixed times. <br><br><strong><i><u>AssignedEmployees : </u></i></strong>The Employees attached to plans.",
    "DetailsNotes": "</u></i></strong><br><strong><i><u>Code : </u></i></strong>Enter the code required to be assigned to the attendance plan. <br><br><strong><i><u>English Name : </u></i></strong>Enter the description of the attendance plan in the English Language. <br><br><strong><i><u>Arabic Name : </u></i></strong>Enter the description of the attendance plan in the Arabic Language. <br><br><strong><i><u>Plan Type:</u></i></strong> Select the method of calculating the working hours in the attendance plan by marking one of the attached radio buttons: <br><br><strong><i><u>• Variable Hours: </u></i></strong>The employees variable hours (e.g. from 8 am to 5 pm with the exception of coming late with the condition of substituting these hours during the week or the month according to the selection). <br><br><strong><i><u>• Calculated Hours: </u></i></strong>Calculating the number of working hours for the employee and pay them according to each employee’s hour rate. <br><br><strong><i><u>• Static Hours: </u></i></strong>The employees fixed hours (e.g. from 8 am to 5 pm). <br><br><strong><i><u>• Free Hours: </u></i></strong>Specify the number of hours that the employees should spend at work without setting fixed times. <br><br><strong><i><u>Related Shifts: </u></i></strong>The Shifts which is Related to this plan. <br><br><strong><i><u>• Direct Range :</u></i></strong> The default not checked which means will  apply multi ranges in case the user need to get the data directly from the related range , the user has to checked this flag. <br><br><strong><i><u>•Shifts: </u></i></strong>The Code and Name of the Shift<br><br><strong><i><u> Is Default: </u></i></strong>The Default Shift for this Plan<br><br><strong><i><u>Late Permission : </u></i></strong>Mark this check box in case you require to give the authority to the employees to be late on the level of a specified period and some fields will be activated as follows:<br><br><strong><i><u>• Deduct from Period Excuses: </u></i></strong>Mark this check box in case you require to deduct the late minutes from the excuses specified for the employees within the selected period. <br><br><strong><i><u>• Period Dates: </u></i></strong>Specify the time period during the month within which the late permission will be applied by clicking on the down arrow next to <strong>From</strong> and <strong>To</strong>, to open the drop-down list and select the required range of days.<br><br><strong><i><u>• Apply if Late Min. Less Than: </u></i></strong> Enter the number of late minutes after which the late permission feature should not be applied.<br><br><strong><i><u>• Min. Allowed Late: </u></i></strong> Enter the number of late minutes allowed in the attendance plan.<br><br><strong><i><u>Not Apply Formal Vacation: </u></i></strong>Mark this check box in case you require to make the attendance plan not subject to any formal vacation. ",
