    "Note": " <br><strong><i><u> Apply Incomplete overall Shifts and plans : </u></i></strong>Mark this check box in case you require to make the transaction of applying incomplete transactions to all attendance plans and shifts by default when dealing with the system. <br><br><strong><i><u> Incomplete Transaction : </u></i></strong>Mark this check box in case you want to apply the use of incomplete transactions when dealing with the system i.e. unregistered fingerprints (attend/leave).  <br><br><strong><i><u> Incomplete In : </u></i></strong>Mark this check box in case you want to apply the use of incomplete transactions with the In only when dealing with the system i.e. unregistered fingerprints (attend).<br><br><strong><i><u> Incomplete Out : </u></i></strong>Mark this check box in case you want to apply the use of incomplete transactions with the Out only when dealing with the system i.e. unregistered fingerprints (Leave). <br><br><strong><i><u> Enable Calculation Way In Attendance Calculation: </u></i></strong>Mark this check box in case you want to activate the ability to specify the method of calculating fingerprints in the Attendance Calculation screen.<br><br><strong><i><u> Incomplete Regulation : </u></i></strong>Mark this check box in case you require to apply the defined personnel affairs regulation when dealing with the system. <br><br><strong><i><u> Calculate vacation with attendance : </u></i></strong>Mark this check box in case you want to take into consideration the vacation days when calculating employee attendance. <br><br><strong><i><u> Allowance Leave is applied : </u></i></strong>Mark this check box and the following fields related to the allowance leave will be displayed.<br>  <br><strong><i><u>Apply Other Substitution (Transportation, Meal/…: </u></i></strong>Mark this check box in case you want to make the applying of the substitution transaction activated when dealing with the system, and following field will be activated: <br> <br><strong><i><u> •  Employee Will Take Transportation Substitute if Daily Worked Hours Equal: </u></i></strong> Enter the number of hours which when spent at work over than the actual hours of the day, the employee will receive a substitution.  <br><br><strong><i><u> Number of working hours by day (Info Data): </u></i></strong>Enter the default number of working hours as information to calculate the number of daily working hours for the employee based on it. <br> <br><strong><i><u>Close opened periods in the month before date: </u></i></strong>Enter the date on which the month of attendance of the employees will be automatically closed by clicking on the calendar icon located on the left side of the field and selecting the required date from the calendar.   ",
