    "MachineType": "Machine Type",
    "ConnectionType": "Connection Type",
    "IPAddress": "IP Address",
    "ConnectionKey": "Connection Key",
    "Port": "Port",
    "BaudRate": "Baud Rate",
    "Comment": "Comment",
    "Active": "Active",
    "Automatic": "Automatic",
    "Notes": "<strong><i><u>Machine Definition : </u></i></strong><br><br><strong><i><u>•Test Connection: </u></i></strong> To test the machine connection , the icon will turn to green when the connection with the machine is successful, and it will remain red when the test connection failed.<br><br><strong><i><u>•Machine: </u></i></strong> Enter the code of machine that refers to the name of the machine.<br><br><strong><i><u>•Machine Type: </u></i></strong>Choose the type of the machine.<br><br><strong><i><u>•Connection Type: </u></i></strong>: Choose the type of connection.<br><br><strong><i><u>•IP Address : </u></i></strong>enter machine’s IP address.<br><br><strong><i><u>•Connection Key: </u></i></strong>Enter the key of the connection.<br><br><strong><i><u>•Port: </u></i></strong>Enter the port of the machine.<br><br><strong><i><u>•Baud Rate: </u></i></strong>Choose the speed rate at which a modem can transmit data.<br><br><strong><i><u>•Comment: </u></i></strong>Enter any comments related to the machine.<br><br><strong><i><u>•Active: </u></i></strong>Check if the machine is active to connect.<strong><i><u><br><br>Database Connection: </u></i></strong><br><br><strong><i><u>•Test Connection: </u></i></strong> To test the Database Connection, the icon will turn to green when the connection with Database is successful, and it will remain red when the test connection failed.<br><br><strong><i><u>•Database Type: </u></i></strong>This is the type of database (oracle or SQL).<br><br><strong><i><u>•Username: </u></i></strong>Enter user name .<br><br><strong><i><u>•Password: </u></i></strong>Enter password.<br><br><strong><i><u>•Database Address: </u></i></strong>Enter the IP address of the database .<br><br><strong><i><u>•Database Port : </u></i></strong> Enter the port of the database.<br><br><strong><i><u>•Database Service Name: </u></i></strong>Enter the service name of the database.<br><br><strong><i><u>•Database TSN Name : </u></i></strong>enter the TSN name of the database.<br><br><strong><i><u>•Comment: </u></i></strong>Enter any comments related to the database connection.<br><br><strong><i><u>•Active: </u></i></strong>Check if the database is active to connect.<br><br><strong><i><u>•Database Name: </u></i></strong>Enter the name of the database.<br><br><strong><i><u>•Data Source: </u></i></strong>enter IP address of database ."
  },
  "AttendanceFromConnection":{
    "ManualAttendanceFromConnection":"Manual Attendance From Connection",
    "database":"Database",
    "DateFromTo":"Date From / To",
    "Start":"Start",
    "Clear":"Clear",
    "CardId":"Card ID",
    "Employee":"Code Number | Employee ",
    "ATTENDANCE_TYPE":"Type",
    "ATTENDANCE_TIME":"Time",
    "ATTENDANCE_DATE":"Date",
    "Action":"Action",
    "Machine":"Machine",
    "Mobile":"Mobile",
    "Clockify":"Clockify",
    "DataSource": "Source",
    "Notes":"<strong><i><u>Database : </u></i></strong><br><br><strong><i><u>•Database: </u></i></strong>Select database.<br><br><strong><i><u>•Date From / To : </u></i></strong>  Enter the range of dates.<br><br><strong><i><u>•Start: </u></i></strong> Click on Start to get the data that exist in the entered range of dates in Date From / To fields.<br><br><strong><i><u>•Clear : </u></i></strong>Click on Clear to delete the data.<br><br><strong><i><u>•Test Connection Icon:  </u></i></strong>To test the connection with the database. It converts to green icon when the connection with the database is successful while giving the notification (Succeeded to Connect) and remains red with the notification (Failed to Connect) when the connection failed.<br><br><strong><i><u>Date From To, Start button, Clear button are all disable based on the test connection: </u></i></strong>When the connection succeeds the convert to be enabled.<br><br><strong><i><u>Machine : </u></i></strong><br><br><strong><i><u>•Machine: </u></i></strong>Select the machine.<br><br><strong><i><u>•Action : </u></i></strong>  Select the action.<br><br><strong><i><u>•Start: </u></i></strong> Click on Start to get the data from the machine and save it in database.<br><br><strong><i><u>•Clear: </u></i></strong>Click on Clear to delete the data from the machine.<br><br><strong><i><u>•Test Connection Icon:  </u></i></strong>To test the connection with the machine. It converts to green icon when the connection with the machine is successful while giving the notification (Succeeded to Connect) and remains red with the notification (Failed to Connect) when the connection failed.<br><br><strong><i><u>Date From To, Start button, Clear button are all disable based on the test connection:</u></i></strong>When the connection succeeds the convert to be enabled."
  },
